<page>
	<title level="2">Questions - Content Questions</title>
<introduction>Content questions differ from Yes/No questions in that they contain an interrogative word or phrase, known as <i>wh</i>-phrases in English because they almost all begin with <example>wh</example> (<example>who</example>, <example>what</example>, <example>why</example>, <example>where</example>, <example>when</example>, <example>how</example>, <example>which</example>).</introduction>
	<form section="q">
<prompt>Key a list of the interrogative words in your language and their gloss here:</prompt>
<textBox id="QWhWords" dataItem="whWords"/>
<!-- NB: we really need a new kind of data box for these: one that allows for an unlimited number of paired data items -->
<instruction>Go to the lexicon and mark each of the interrogative words with the feature <feature>wh</feature>.</instruction>
